acdVSetConfigEntry.name: acdVSetConfigEntry
acdVSetConfigEntry.description: An entry consisting of all settings to a VLAN set.

acdVSetConfigPolicyListID.description: This object identifies for which Policy list of this VLAN set.

acdVSetConfigID.name: acdVSetConfigID
acdVSetConfigID.description: Unique value for each VLAN set instance.

acdVSetConfigRowStatus.name: acdVSetConfigRowStatus
acdVSetConfigRowStatus.description: All columns must have a valid value before a row can be activated. To create a new VLAN set you shall provide the a unique name, the type and policy list id for an empty row with the RowStatus set to Create and Go. To delete the VLAN set you need to set the RowStatus to destroy.

acdVSetConfigName.name: acdVSetConfigName
acdVSetConfigName.description: This is a string to uniquely identify the VLAN set.

acdVSetConfigVlanIDs0to1023.name: acdVSetConfigVlanIDs0to1023
acdVSetConfigVlanIDs0to1023.description: Each octet specifies a set of eight VLANs, the first octet specifying VLAN ID 0 through 7, and so on. Within each octet, the most significant bit represents the lowest numbered VLAN ID. If that bit has a value of '1' then that VLAN is included in the set of VLANs; the VLAN is not included otherwise.
